-- Polish Tourist Missing in Georgia After Ravine Fall, Imedi Says
-- B y   H e l e n a   B e d w e l l
-- 2012-08-20T11:17:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/polish-tourist-missing-in-georgia-after-ravine-fall-imedi-says.html
Georgian rescuers are searching for
a Polish woman who fell into a ravine in the northwest region of
Svaneti, the Imedi TV channel reported.  The tourist, who has not been identified, left her vehicle
in the village of Kala yesterday and decided to walk to the
nearby Ushguli area before she fell, the broadcaster, based in
the capital, Tbilisi, said today, citing an eyewitness.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helena Bedwell in Tbilisi at 
 hbedwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  